time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Chinese
---

Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have ½ tsp (1 tsp for 4 servings). Trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise into ½-inch-thick rounds. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for
4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook, covered, until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and minced
ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Add zucchini, @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}, chickpeas, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until cabbage is slightly wilted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add @coconut milk{1} and ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4); cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a fork.

Divide rice between bowls; top with curry. Garnish with scallion greens and a squeeze of lime juice. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> This vegan Thai green curry with chickpeas plus zucchini, cabbage, rice & lime
> is a quick and flavorful plant-based dinner idea that comes together in just
> 20 minutes!